Detailed Description

LibraryItem class is used to create the hierarchical structure of component library.

component library is a hierarchical structure consisting of vendors, libraries, names and versions. One instance knows its children and can provide access to them.

LibraryItem * LibraryItem::findHighestUnique ( LibraryItem *  childItem = 0  ) 

Find the highest level LibraryItem that still identifies a single item.

This function checks if there are other children. If no other children are found then this function calls parent item to check if it can be used to identify a single item.

Parameters:
childItem Pointer to item that is currently the highest possible item.
